parameters:
And so, we were moved from the Ryuda headquarters and left
to stay in this place.

By spending time here, we were made painfully aware that
there was no deceit in Zuuteruka's words.

It was a place filled with the anguish not only of us but
also of Zuuteruka, and the Ryuda recruits who could be
thrown into a harsh reality like this training camp at the
flick of a finger by the main forces.

Segi and I took customers as Zuuteruka had told us to. There
was no other choice.

The customers were Ryuda recruits. Most of them were beasts
who would pounce on a woman's body unconditionally at the
sight of one.

However, some felt sorrow in the harsh reality and sought
solace from us.

In the midst of despair, sorrow, and anxiety about tomorrow
filling the hearts of us and the Ryuda recruits, there was
an encounter.

At that time, I had no way of knowing that this encounter
would change the course of this reality.
\N<Princess Consort Suia>...What's wrong? Why are you silent?
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Ah, I see. Perhaps you're not interested because I'm older?

\N<Princess Consort Suia>If you were looking forward to this with excitement, then I
apologize.

\N<Ryuda Recruit>No, it's not that you're older... I don't see you like that
at all... rather, for me, that...
\N<Princess Consort Suia>...So what will you do? Will you leave for tonight...?
\N<Ryuda Recruit>N-no... I mean, please take care of me...
\N<Ryuda Recruit>S-sorry... why at a time like this...

\N<Ryuda Recruit>It's strange... this is strange, right? I've never... not
even once normally...

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Hehe, there's no need to rush. We have time. Let's take it
slow.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>But what happened? With the way you were acting before, do
you really not fancy me?

\N<Ryuda Recruit>That's ridiculous! It's just that... I'm embarrassed to say
this but it's my first time with such acts... I don't really
understand.

\N<Ryuda Recruit>So it's not that you lack charm! It's just that I might have
made you feel uncomfortable... I'm sorry...!
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Uncomfortable? You are such a pure person.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>I'm not sure if I can satisfy someone as pure as you, but
perhaps this is fate. I will serve you to the best of my
ability.

\N<Princess Consort Suia><Princess Consort Suia> If you consider my feelings, then
perhaps you should think of tonight as a reward from me.

\N<Princess Consort Suia><Princess Consort Suia> Therefore... you may indulge in my
body to your heart's content tonight without worry.
\N<Princess Consort Suia><Princess Consort Suia> Now... won't you come?
\N<Seno><Seno> Is that so... such a thing...

\N<Princess Consort Suia><Princess Consort Suia> Yes, it seems that even I have been
swayed by emotion, albeit slightly.
\N<Seno><Seno> It's not surprising. I'm sure I would...

\N<Former Duchy Soldier><Former Duchy Soldier> Excuse me, I have something to
discuss with the two of you...

\N<Seno><Seno> What is it? A guest? As you can see, we're closed for
the night. Please come back tomorrow.

\N<Seno><Seno> What do you want exactly? You must have something to
say, right? Standing there won't explain anything.

\N<Former Duchy Soldier><Former Duchy Soldier> It's about the two of you... surely
you must have some thoughts on the matter?

\N<Seno><Seno> Thoughts...? What are you talking about out of the
blue?

\N<Former Duchy Soldier><Former Duchy Soldier> You won't... You won't be content
with staying here forever, right...!?

\N<Seno><Seno> Huh, is that what this is about? And what if we were
content with it?

\N<Former Duchy Soldier><Former Duchy Soldier> Even if that were the case... we
believe in you both. We want to follow wherever you lead.

\N<Seno><Seno> That's nice to hear. Even in such a state as this,
huh?

\N<Former Duchy Soldier><Former Duchy Soldier> The two of you once healed us who
betrayed our country... you protected us from Lyuda's
persecution.

\N<Former Duchy Soldier><Former Duchy Soldier> Without your intercession and pleas,
we would have been hanged long ago.

\N<Seno><Seno> Thank you. I didn't expect to hear such words here.
I'll remember what you've done.

\N<Seno><Seno> But unfortunately, we've given up on a lot of things
already.

\N<Former Duchy Soldier><Former Duchy Soldier> That can't be... If there's any
clever plan, please let us know. We won't leak any secrets
to anyone...

\N<Seno><Seno> Haha, that's even more delightful. That's why we
can't let loyal subjects like you be persecuted by Lyuda.

\N<Seno><Seno> Now, go back to your posts before other Lyuda
soldiers find you.

It was supposed to be just another night... a night like
many others since becoming prisoners.

However... still. That night, a certain thought definitely
crossed our minds...

Time passed... and as if it were only natural, we found
ourselves pregnant with a child of Lyuda for who knows how
many times.

Gazing at my ever-growing belly, which could not even
determine its father, with somewhat detached eyes... that
thought continued to haunt my mind.
It happened on a certain day...

\N<Zuuteruka><Zuuteruka> Hey, how are you feeling? I'm counting on you
again today, alright?</Zuuteruka>

\N<Princess Consort Suia><Princess Consort Suia> What exactly should I be counted on
for? I will simply fulfill my duties as usual.</Princess
Consort Suia>

\N<Zuuteruka><Zuuteruka> It's commendable, but unfortunately, that won't
do tonight. After all, today's guest is someone
special.</Zuuteruka>
\N<Zuuteruka>Well, now that it's decided, before that...
\N<Princess Consort Suia>...What do you intend to do?

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, what do you want to do? This man is a warrior who
showed excellent performance at the recent training
assembly. To honor his achievements, I want you to serve him
thoroughly tonight.
\N<Orugi>Zuuteruka, what the hell are you planning?

\N<Zuuteruka>Just as you see, I'm honoring the master's achievements by
assigning him my very best woman.

\N<Orugi>I don't know what you're trying to do, but it's futile.
Attempts to coax or entice me will not work.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, as stubborn as ever. Well, even a little fun won't
be a waste. Let loose a bit and enjoy yourself.
At that moment... the thought that grazed my mind...

The moment I saw the subject of my once absolute trust. It
turned into... certainty.
Now is the time... I thought.

If a small and powerless person like me could ever intervene
in fate, then the time would be now... I thought.
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Excuse me... I will proceed.
\N<Orugi>...stop it. You have someone you love, don't you...?

\N<Princess Consort Suia>I appreciate your concern. However... your pity is
unnecessary. I am doing this for the sake of that loved one.
\N<Princess Consort Suia>That's why I cannot afford to be rejected by you here.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Regardless of your true intentions, I shall fulfill my duty
as Lyuda's mistress.
\N<Orugi>...? I don't understand what you're saying...

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Is that so... then I will make you feel inclined, even if by
force.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, it's better if you don't refuse every little thing
and just do what needs to be done, right?
\N<Orugi>What are you saying, don't mess around... stop this.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, but it seems like the lady is quite willing, isn't
she?

\N<Princess Consort Suia>...So you're still not inclined? Could it be because of a
lack of charm on my part?

\N<Orugi>No... that's not it. You are attractive. Even through a
mask, your charm is more than evident. You're too good for a
brute like me.
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Even if it's flattery, I'm happy... Thank you very much.

\N<Orugi>It's not flattery, it's the truth. That's why I want you to
take care of yourself.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>I'm happy... but now is not the time to indulge in emotions.
When the time comes, we shall speak our minds freely.
\N<Orugi>Th-that voice... could it be... could it really be...
\N<Princess Consort Suia>It's been a long time... Orugi.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, a reunion of former master and servant, huh? What
are you both feeling right now?

\N<Orugi>So it really is you, Princess Consort...! Are you
unharmed...? I have been worried about you day and night...!
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Is that concern as a former lord? Or as a woman?

\N<Princess Consort Suia>I told you, now is not the time to reminisce about our
reunion. I am here as a courtesan of Lyuda, serving you.

\N<Orugi>Please stop...! Recognizing you in that state and still such
indecency...! Do you intend to make me a traitor, Princess
Consort...!?

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Of course not... Who would treat a loyalist like you so
carelessly. I said I am doing this for the sake of someone I
love.
\N<Orugi>For the sake of someone you love...
\N<Orugi>...Could it be... Princess Consort, are you...
\N<Princess Consort Suia>...I'll leave the rest to your imagination.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Yes... there's no need for hesitation. Please do as you
wish.

\N<Orugi>Engaging in such acts... I will have no face to show to my
wife and daughter, and to Lord Yuia. However... I would like
to indulge in your words for now, Princess Consort.

\N<Orugi>And when this is over... I will accept any punishment that
comes then.
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Fufu... There's no need to be so formal, it's fine.
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Orugi... You've had a hard time until now.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Ah... right, it's okay. There's no need to worry. If it's
about Seno, there's no need for concern. Just like me, she
is also safe.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Since becoming prisoners of Lyuda, we have survived day and
night like this. Both me... and Seno.

\N<Orugi>Even if that were the case... how could I possibly despise
the Princess Consort or my wife?

\N<Orugi>Rather than such feelings, my heart is filled with emotion
at being able to meet the Princess Consort alive again.
Similarly, I am filled with anticipation for the day I can
speak with my wife again.
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Yes... you may. But gently, okay...?
\N<Princess Consort Suia>You're quite forceful, aren't you?

\N<Princess Consort Suia>I-I'm sorry... I was just a bit startled. When you asked if
you could touch me, I thought you meant... my stomach.

\N<Orugi>Then, once again... Princess Consort. May I touch the place
where your child resides...?

\N<Orugi>I apologize once more. It's a bit funny for me to say this,
but I am a bit of a brute.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Hehe... it's fine. Proceed as you wish. Right now... I am
your woman, after all.
\N<Princess Consort Suia>But in return... please hold my shoulders firmly, okay...?

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Orugi... I'm sorry. You must have wanted to be intimate like
this with Seno instead.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Right now, I'm sure a whirlwind of emotions is swirling
inside you. I can only imagine...
\N<Princess Consort Suia>But please... please don't hate Seno.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Just like me, she chose a path of living shame for an
unwavering purpose...
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Yes... to live and meet you again.

\N<Orugi>As I said before, there's no way I could hate my wife. She
is my pride and joy...

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Is that so... I'm glad. She will surely be happy to hear
that.

\N<Orugi>...What's the matter? If there's anywhere you don't want me
to touch, please don't hesitate to tell me. I am clumsy,
after all.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>No... it's not that. It's just that... I found it a little
funny.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Yes, the sight of you, known as a mighty warrior, looking
like a baby seeking comfort from its mother at night...

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Clinging to my chest so eagerly... that sight was so
endearing.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Though I must say... it's rude of me to call a man of your
stature 'endearing'. That was improper of me... let me
apologize right this way.

\N<Orugi>It didn't bother me in the slightest... but did you dislike
it?

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Not at all... I want you to continue even more. To be
honest... it makes me happy. It means that I still have some
allure as a woman left in me.
\N<Orugi>Clinging like a baby in a daze... Perhaps you're right.

\N<Orugi>The days when I was captured by Ryuda and forced to fight in
their training battles were harsh. There was the smell of
death, but never the sweet scent of a woman's breast.
\N<Orugi>So if it belongs to the Princess Consort... all the more so.

\N<Orugi>It's odd to say this about myself... but perhaps I had pent-
up feelings.

\N<Orugi>So... that, getting carried away is perhaps inevitable for
me...

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Is that so... I must have caused you feelings that can't be
fully compensated with just this.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Otherwise, unless it were Seno, there's no way you would be
so captivated by my body.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>To make up for your hardships, if I am sufficient... you may
do as you please with me.
\N<Orugi>No... it's not solely because I was pent-up.

\N<Orugi>The castle guards... they were in love, though they never
spoke of it... with you.
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Fufu, Orugi... could it be that you too?
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Fufu, it's alright. It was a mean question on my part...

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Fufu... don't embarrass a woman, will you? Besides... you
seem to be suffering too.
\N<Princess Consort Suia>There's no need to hold back... let it out plentifully.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Tainted by Ryuda's villains as I am... I'm anxious whether I
can satisfy you.

\N<Orugi>I don't understand what you mean. I have never seen anything
as beautiful as this.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>...I'm happy. But... saying such things will make Seno
jealous...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe! You really did it! You plunged into the beautiful
Princess Consort! Where's the pride of a former loyal
retainer, huh?

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, watch this, guys. No matter how noble the excuses a
simpleton makes, this is how it goes. When a woman desperate
for it spreads her legs for him, a man's resolve easily
breaks.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Orugi... I'm glad you're still alive... But... right now, I
have nothing to offer you...
\N<Princess Consort Suia>So... at least... let this... serve as a reward...
\N<Orugi>Such a thing... is too great a reward for someone like me...

\N<Orugi>Such a thing... is too great a reward for someone like me...
I, on the other hand, should not be doing this to the
Princess Consort...

\N<Orugi>To think that someone as uncouth as me would be accepted by
you without any disgust... It's an honor beyond measure...
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Fufu... What are you saying? I'm not enduring anything...

\N<Princess Consort Suia>I'm gladly offering myself to you... Besides, being with a
warrior once renowned throughout the kingdom... What is
there to dislike?

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Fufu... It's inelegant to use such formalities in the
bedroom, don't you think?
\N<Princess Consort Suia>For tonight at least... please call me Suia?

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Orugi... I should be the one apologizing... I can't excite
you like your wife Seno does.
\N<Orugi>What are you saying... I am committed to only one wife...

\N<Orugi>I am a simple warrior who knows no other woman... I wonder
if I can truly serve the Princess Consort well enough...
\N<Princess Consort Suia>It's Suia... Just Suia for tonight... please?
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Even so... fufu. Perhaps we are quite similar...
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Hey... Orugi. Will you kiss me first?

\N<Princess Consort Suia>At this point, being reserved is just inelegant...
Besides... I want you to reassure me.
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Because... I've been feeling anxious.
\N<Orugi>If my existence can be of any use to you...
\N<Princess Consort Suia>It's okay... Give me all of you...
\N<Princess Consort Suia>...It's fine. No, rather... I want to ask for it myself...

\N<Princess Consort Suia>To think that my tainted body could excite you makes me
happy. So... at least let me guide you to the end...

\N<Princess Consort Suia>...Right? Let me believe that the life within me now is the
life you've given me tonight...
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Ha... aah... fufu, that was a lot, wasn't it...?

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Fufu, what are you apologizing for...? Have I become your
woman now, I wonder...?

\N<Princess Consort Suia>But... it's a pity. I'm at a disadvantage when Seno is
involved, aren't I? In other words... tonight is the only
night I can have you all to myself.
\N<Princess Consort Suia>So... perhaps I shall monopolize you just for tonight? Fufu.
\N<Princess Consort Suia>So... right? Tonight... you will look only at me?

\N<Zuuteruka>Hey, how long do you two plan to keep this up? Isn't it
about time you separated? You're not a pair of monkeys
who've just learned how.

\N<Orugi>It was you who said to let loose and enjoy ourselves. I'm
merely doing so without reservation...

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Ah, ahn... That's right. It's rude to interfere with the
coupling of a man and a woman...?

\N<Orugi>As the Princess Consort says. Besides, an opportunity like
this doesn't come often, so I shall indulge to my heart's
content.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hmph, there's a limit even for someone as unreachable as she
was. Truly, a loyal retainer would be appalled.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>It's precisely because he was once a subject... mmm... that
he's so aroused tonight...

\N<Princess Consort Suia>If you can't understand that... haa... ah. Zuuteruka...
you're still quite naive, aren't you?

\N<Orugi>Exactly... It's because of the love that was hidden away
that one burns with passion. Like with the Princess Consort
tonight... and myself.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Ha... ah... Orugi... love me more... show me more of your
love...

\N<Princess Consort Suia>If you say you've longed for me... then make me feel it
more...?

\N<Zuuteruka>Anyway, that's enough. Put away that filthy thing that's
still standing up.
